  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "Determining whether a guy likes you or is just using you can be challenging, but there are several signs you can look for to help clarify his intentions. Here are some tips:\n\n1. **Consistency in Communication**:\n   - If he likes you: He will consistently initiate contact, be interested in your life, and maintain conversations.\n   - If he is using you: His communication might be sporadic or mostly focused on what he needs from you.\n\n2. **Investment in Getting to Know You**:\n   - If he likes you: He will want to know about your interests, feelings, and experiences.\n   - If he is using you: He might not show interest in your personal stories or emotions.\n\n3. **Time and Effort**:\n   - If he likes you: He will make an effort to spend time with you and participate in activities that matter to you.\n   - If he is using you: He may only spend time with you when it is convenient for him or when he needs something.\n\n4. **Respect and Support**:\n   - If he likes you: He will respect your boundaries, and be supportive of your goals and decisions.\n   - If he is using you: He might disregard your boundaries and be unsupportive unless it benefits him.\n\n5. **Sharing Personal Details**:\n   - If he likes you: He will share personal stories, thoughts, and feelings with you, building a deeper connection.\n   - If he is using you: He might be secretive or avoid deeper conversations.\n\n6. **Plans for the Future**:\n   - If he likes you: He will include you in his future plans and discuss long-term possibilities.\n   - If he is using you: He might avoid talking about the future or make vague promises.\n\n7. **Physical Affection**:\n   - If he likes you: Physical affection comes naturally and is accompanied by emotional closeness.\n   - If he is using you: Physical contact may seem forced or be the main focus of the relationship without emotional depth.\n\n8. **Actions Over Words**:\n   - If he likes you: His actions will align with his words, showing genuine interest and care.\n   - If he is using you: He might say the right things but his actions don't match up, indicating insincerity.\n\n9. **Treatment during Tough Times**:\n   - If he likes you: He will stand by you during difficult times and offer support.\n   - If he is using you: He might disappear when you need help or only be around when things are easy.\n\nIf these signs point towards him using you rather than genuinely liking you, it\u2019s important to address the situation and communicate your feelings. Trust your instincts and prioritize your emotional well-being in any relationship.",
